Message.MsgText: MULTIPLE_DESTS_FOUND_CWSJA0028=CWSJA0028E: Multiple destinations found.
Message.Explanation: Only one instance of a destination should exist within the scope specified, yet more than one instance has been located.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that destinations have unique configuration data within an administrative domain.

Message.MsgText: SERVER_NOT_CLUSTER_MEMBER_CWSJA0129=CWSJA0129E: The server "{1}" on node "{0}" is not a member of the cluster "{2}".
Message.Explanation: The node and server supplied to the command do not correspond to a member of the cluster supplied.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that you used the correct spelling for the node, server and cluster name, and that the server is a member of the cluster.

Message.MsgText: NO_FAILOVER_MEANS_NO_FAILBACK_CWSJA0119=CWSJA0119E: If a messaging engine can not fail over, it can not fail back.
Message.Explanation: The failover parameter is set to false, but the failback parameter is set to true.
Message.UserResponse: Either set the failback parameter to false, or set the failover parameter to true.

Message.MsgText: NO_COMMAND_RESULT_CWSJA1200=CWSJA1200E: The {0} command did not return a result.
Message.Explanation: Internal error. The specified command did not return a result.
Message.UserResponse: Please contact your system administrator to resolve this problem.

Message.MsgText: CONFIG_ARCHIVE_CELL_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA0800=CWSJA0800E: No cells found in configuration archive.
Message.Explanation: The configuration archive does not contain any cells.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the configuration archive contains a cell.

Message.MsgText: NODE_VERSION_NOT_VALID_FOR_WMQSERVER_CWSJA0615=CWSJA0615E: node parameter specifies a pre version 6.1 node, which is not valid for a WebSphere MQ mediation execution point
Message.Explanation: The node parameter specifies a WebSphere Application Server Version 6.0 node. This node cannot host a mediation execution point for a WebSphere MQ mediated destination.
Message.UserResponse: Select a node that is of Version 6.1 or later.

Message.MsgText: SERVER_NOT_COMPATABLE_WITH_MEDIATION_SECURITY_CWSJA0140=CWSJA0140E: The server {0} on node {1} does not support the useServerIdForMediations option configured for bus {2}.
Message.Explanation: The server could not be added to the bus because the bus has been configured to use the server identity for mediations, but the server resides on a pre-7.0 WebSphere Application Server Version node. The useServerIdForMediations is not compatible with pre-Version 7.0 nodes.
Message.UserResponse: Change the bus to use an authentication alias for mediations instead of the server identity.

Message.MsgText: NO_BUS_MEMBER_TARGET_CWSJA0051=CWSJA0051E: No bus member target found for WebSphere MQ server "{0}" on bus "{1}".
Message.Explanation: When added to a bus, a WebSphere MQ server should have one bus member target. None was found.
Message.UserResponse: Report this problem to your system administrator.

Message.MsgText: FAILED_TO_GET_RELIABILITY_VALUES_CWSJA0039=CWSJA0039E: Failed to determine values for "reliability" and "maxReliability".
Message.Explanation: An internal error occurred while trying to determine values for the reliability and maxReliability parameters.
Message.UserResponse: Report this problem to your system administrator.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_SECURITY_EXIT_PARAMETERS_SUPPLIED_CWSJA1615=CWSJA1615E: The "securityExitInit" parameter can only be supplied if the "securityExit" parameter is supplied.
Message.Explanation: The "securityExitInit" parameter can only be supplied if the "securityExit" parameter is supplied.
Message.UserResponse: Supply the "securityExit" parameter or do not suplly the "securityExitInit" parameter.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_DESTINATION_PROPERTY_VALUE_CWSJA0155=CWSJA0155E: The supplied mediationPoints are not valid for the specified target destination. Each mediation point must be a SIBMediationPoint belonging to the target queue.
Message.Explanation: Each mediation point must be a SIBMediationPoint belonging to the target queue.
Message.UserResponse: Identify any non valid mediation point(s) and correct the list.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_DESTINATION_PROPERTY_VALUE_CWSJA0151=CWSJA0151E: The supplied queuePoints are not valid for the specified target destination. Each queue point must be a SIBQueueLocalizationPoint belonging to the target queue.
Message.Explanation: Each queue point must be a SIBQueueLocalizationPoint belonging to the target queue.
Message.UserResponse: Identify any non valid queue point(s) and correct the list.

Message.MsgText: ENGINE_NOT_FOUND_FOR_BUS_CWSJA0104=CWSJA0104E: No messaging engines found at scope "{0}" for bus "{1}".
Message.Explanation: The operation could not be invoked because no messaging engines exist at the specified scope for the given bus.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that there is a messaging engine at the specified scope for the given bus.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_PARAM_COMBINATION_CWSJA2601=CWSJA2601E: Incorrect parameter combination supplied : node name = "{0}", server name = "{1}", cluster name = "{2}".
Message.Explanation: The command should specify a specific server or a cluster. To specify a server a valid node name and server name must be provided. To specify a cluster just the cluster name should be provided.
Message.UserResponse: Rerun the command specifying either a node and server name, or a cluster name.

Message.MsgText: NULL_TEMPLATE_ID_CWSJA1400=CWSJA1400E: Application server template ID is null.
Message.Explanation: Internal error. The application server template ID is null.
Message.UserResponse: Please contact your system administrator to resolve this problem.

Message.MsgText: MEDIATE_DESTINATION_PARAMETERS_INCORRECT_CWSJA0611=CWSJA0611E: When supplying "wmqServer" parameter it must be supplied with either "node" and "server" parameters or "cluster" parameter.
Message.Explanation: Invalid parameters have been supplied to the command. When specifying the wmqServer parameter, you must specify execution point where the mediation will run.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the wmqServer parameter is supplied with either the node and server parameters, or the cluster parameter.

Message.MsgText: MULTIPLE_BUSMEMBERS_FOUND_CWSJA0024=CWSJA0024E: Multiple bus members found.
Message.Explanation: Only one instance of a bus member should exist within the scope specified, yet more than one instance has been located.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that bus members have unique configuration data within an administrative domain.

Message.MsgText: DEST_NOT_IN_MQ_CWSJA0618=CWSJA0618E: When specifying a value of true for parameter "externallyMediated" the destination being mediated must be assigned to WebSphere MQ.
Message.Explanation: Externally mediating destinations are only supported for destinations that are localized in WebSphere MQ.
Message.UserResponse: Set the externallyMediated parameter to false, or mediate a destination that is assigned to WebSphere MQ.

Message.MsgText: GLOBAL_SECURITY_DISABLED_CWSJA0072=CWSJA0072E: Bus security has been specified to be enabled, but administrative security is disabled.
Message.Explanation: You cannot set the busSecurity parameter to true unless you also enable administrative security.
Message.UserResponse: Either use the administrative console to enable administrative security, or set the busSecurity parameter to false.

Message.MsgText: MEDIATE_DESTINATION_PARAMETERS_INCORRECT_CWSJA0605=CWSJA0605E: Supply either "node" and "server" parameters or "cluster" parameter.
Message.Explanation: Null parameters have been supplied to the command.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that either the node and server parameters, or the cluster parameter, is supplied to the command.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_CREATE_JMSQ_NAME_CWSJA0208=CWSJA0208E: Not allowed to create a SIB JMS queue called "{0}".
Message.Explanation: The name provided for the SIB JMS queue does not adhere to naming restrictions.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the name does not begin with an underscore, and is not empty or null.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_CREATE_ACT_SPEC_NAME_CWSJA0406=CWSJA0406E: Not allowed to create a SIB JMS ActivationSpec called "{0}".
Message.Explanation: The name provided for the SIB JMS ActivationSpec does not adhere to naming restrictions.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the name does not begin with an underscore, and is not empty or null.

Message.MsgText: MQ_SERVERPROXY_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA1603=CWSJA1603E: WebSphere MQ Server Proxy "{0}" not found on Bus {1}.
Message.Explanation: The specified WebSphere MQ server proxy name could not be located within the bus administrative domain.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the WebSphere MQ server proxy name specified is a valid name for an existing WebSphere MQ server proxy. Check that the bus name specified is the correct bus for the WebSphere MQ server proxy.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_ACT_SPEC_FAILING_MSG_DELAY_VALUE_CWSJA0417=CWSJA0417E: The failingMessageDelay value, {0}, is not an valid long value greater than or equal to zero.
Message.Explanation: Valid values are zero or more, which indicate the period of time in milliseconds that passes before a failing message is retried before its maximum failed delivery limit is reached
Message.UserResponse: Specify a value of zero or more.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_DATASOURCE_NAME_CWSJA0161=CWSJA0161E: The test connection to messaging engine datasource {0} cannot be validated.
Message.Explanation: The Test Connection to given datasource cannot be validated.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the datasource name is correct and server process at scope of datasource is running.

Message.MsgText: DESTINATION_ALREADY_MEDIATED_CWSJA0604=CWSJA0604E: Destination "{0}" is already mediated.
Message.Explanation: The destination specified is already mediated, and a destination cannot be mediated twice.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the specified destination is not already mediated before trying to mediate it.

Message.MsgText: DEST_NOT_FOUND_ON_BUS_CWSJA0034=CWSJA0034E: Failed to find destination "{1}" on bus "{0}".
Message.Explanation: The named destination could not be located on the named bus within the administrative domain.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the named destination exists on the named bus.

Message.MsgText: TOO_MANY_BUS_MEMBER_TARGETS_CWSJA0052=CWSJA0052E: Too many bus member targets found for WebSphere MQ server "{0}" on bus "{1}". Number of bus member targets found was {2}.
Message.Explanation: When added to a bus, a WebSphere MQ server should have one bus member target. More than one was found.
Message.UserResponse: Report this problem to your system administrator.

Message.MsgText: SERVER_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA0126=CWSJA0126E: The server "{1}" could not be found on node "{0}".
Message.Explanation: The node and server names that were supplied to the command could not be used to resolve a Server object.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that you used the correct spelling for the node and server names, and that the Server exists in the configuration.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_MESSAGE_STORE_TYPE_COMBINATION_CWSJA0058=CWSJA0058E: Can not specify both a file store AND a data store, or parameters implying such
Message.Explanation: The message store type can be either a file store or a data store, but not both. Therefore parameters relating to both types are not allowed in the same command.
Message.UserResponse: Either remove parameters relating to file store, or to data store.

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_TO_CREATE_BUSMEMBER_CWSJA0005=CWSJA0005E: Unable to create bus member "{0}".
Message.Explanation: An exception was generated attempting to create a bus member with the configuration data provided.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that all configuration data for the bus member is valid.

Message.MsgText: UNRECOGNIZED_PARAM_VALUE_CWSJA0041=CWSJA0041E: Value for parameter "{0}" not recognised.
Message.Explanation: The value supplied for the specified parameter was not recognized.
Message.UserResponse: Run the command again, supplying a valid value.

Message.MsgText: NO_STEP_PARAM_VALUE_CWSJA0038=CWSJA0038E: Required value not supplied for parameter "{2}" of step "{1}" of command "{0}".
Message.Explanation: Either the specified parameter was not supplied for the specified step, or no value was supplied for it.
Message.UserResponse: Run the command again, supplying the missing parameter value for the specified step.

Message.MsgText: CLUSTER_NOT_COMPATABLE_WITH_MEDIATION_SECURITY_CWSJA0141=CWSJA0141E: The cluster {0} does not support the useServerIdForMediations option configured for bus {1}.
Message.Explanation: The cluster could not be added to the bus because the bus has been configured to use the server identity for mediations, but the cluster contains members that reside on pre-7.0 WebSphere Application Server Version node. The useServerIdForMediations is not compatible with pre-Version 7.0 nodes.
Message.UserResponse: Change the bus to use an authentication alias for mediations instead of the server identity.

Message.MsgText: SIB_LINK_EXCEPTION_CWSJA2400=CWSJA2400E: An internal error occured getting the "name" attribute of SIBLink "{0}" : "{1}"
Message.Explanation: An internal error has occurred. See the linked exception for details.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that a valid SIBLink name was specified to the command.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_ACT_SPEC_DEST_TYPE_VALUE_CWSJA0410=CWSJA0410E: {0} is not a valid value for destination type.
Message.Explanation: A value that is not valid has been entered for the destination type property.
Message.UserResponse: Check the documentation for a valid value for this property.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_MESSAGING_SERVER_CWSJA0134=CWSJA0134E: Server supplied does not have a SIB Service.
Message.Explanation: An exception occurred retrieving the SIB Services for the messaging server.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that a SIB Service exists for the messaging server.

Message.MsgText: NO_CELLS_FOUND_CWSJA0803=CWSJA0803E: Configuration contains no cells.
Message.Explanation: The configuration does not contain any cells.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the configuration contains a cell.

Message.MsgText: CHAIN_ALREADY_EXISTS_CWSJA0077=CWSJA0077E: The transport chain name {0} already exists as a permitted transport for the bus {1}.
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to add a transport chain as a permitted transport to the bus. This was unsuccessful because the transport chain is already a permitted transport for the bus.
Message.UserResponse: Add a transport chain with a different name.

Message.MsgText: SERVER_NOT_COMPATIBLE_WITH_BUS_SECURITY_CWSJA0106=CWSJA0106E: Security settings for bus "{0}" are not compatible with server "{1}" because it resides on pre-6.1 node "{2}".
Message.Explanation: The server could not be added to the bus because the server resides on a WebSphere Application Server Version 6.0 node, and bus security settings are not compatible with pre-Version 6.1 nodes. The permitted transport chains setting must not be LISTED or SSL_ENABLED. The Server group must not be in the bus connector role.
Message.UserResponse: Disable security on the named bus, or modify the bus security settings so that bus security is compatible with pre-Version 6.1 nodes, or upgrade the named server so that it resides on a Version 6.1 node.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_RECEIVE_EXIT_PARAMETERS_SUPPLIED_CWSJA1614=CWSJA1614E: The "receiveExitInit" parameter can only be supplied if the "receiveExit" parameter is supplied.
Message.Explanation: The "receiveExitInit" parameter can only be supplied if the "receiveExit" parameter is supplied.
Message.UserResponse: Supply the "receiveExit" parameter or do not suplly the "receiveExitInit" parameter.

Message.MsgText: MULTIPLE_SERVERPROXY_FOUND_CWSJA1604=CWSJA1604E: Multiple instances of WebSphere MQ Server Proxy "{0}" found on Bus {1}.
Message.Explanation: Only one instance of a WebSphere MQ server proxy should exist with the name specified, yet more than one instance has been located.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that WebSphere MQ server proxy names are unique within the administrative domain.

Message.MsgText: MQ_SERVER_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA1600=CWSJA1600E: WebSphere MQ Server "{0}" not found.
Message.Explanation: The specified WebSphere MQ server name could not be located within the administrative domain.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the WebSphere MQ server name specified is a valid name for an existing WebSphere MQ server.

Message.MsgText: ERROR_VALIDATING_RELIABILITY_CWSJA0045=CWSJA0045E: An internal error occurred while validating reliability and maxReliability.
Message.Explanation: An internal error occurred while validating the reliability and maxReliability parameters.
Message.UserResponse: Report this problem to your system administrator.

Message.MsgText: CLUSTER_DOES_NOT_EXIST_CWSJA2602=CWSJA2602E: The cluster {0} does not exist.
Message.Explanation: The specified cluster does not exist.
Message.UserResponse: Rerun the command specifying the name of a cluster that exists.

Message.MsgText: FOREIGN_BUS_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA2000=CWSJA2000E: The Foreign Bus "{0}" could not be found on Bus "{1}"
Message.Explanation: A foreign bus name was supplied to the command that could not be resolved on the specified bus.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the foreign bus supplied to the command exists in the configuration.

Message.MsgText: BAD_BUS_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTE_VALUE_CWSJA0108=CWSJA0108E: The value "{1}" for the permitted transport chains bus security attribute is not valid for bus "{0}" because the bus contains at least one pre-6.1 bus member.
Message.Explanation: Enabling bus security, or changing the named bus security attribute to the indicated value when the bus contains one or more WebSphere Application Server Version 6.0 bus members, is not allowed because the value is not compatible with pre-Version 6.1 bus members. The permitted transport chains setting must not be LISTED or SSL_ENABLED.
Message.UserResponse: Disable security on the named bus, or modify the named security setting to a value that does not conflict with pre-Version 6.1 bus members, or remove all pre-Version 6.1 bus members from the bus.

Message.MsgText: FAILED_TO_FIND_BUS_BY_UUID_CWSJA0030=CWSJA0030E: Failed to find Bus with UUID "{0}".
Message.Explanation: The UUID specified does not belong to a bus in the administrative domain.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the UUID specified belongs to a valid bus.

Message.MsgText: MULTIPLE_MQ_SERVERS_FOUND_CWSJA1601=CWSJA1601E: More than one WebSphere MQ Server named "{0}" found.
Message.Explanation: Only one instance of a WebSphere MQ server should exist with the name specified, yet more than one instance has been found.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that WebSphere MQ server names are unique within the administrative domain.

Message.MsgText: NO_RESOURCE_ADAPTER_CWSJA0200=CWSJA0200E: Failed to get SIB JMS resource adapter at specified scope.
Message.Explanation: An unsuccessful attempt was made to locate a JMS JCA resource adapter installed at the specified scope.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that a JMS JCA resource adapter exists within the specified scope.

Message.MsgText: BUS_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA0125=CWSJA0125E: The bus "{0}" could not be found.
Message.Explanation: The bus name that was supplied to the command could not be resolved to a Bus object.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that you used the correct spelling for the name, and that a Bus with that name exists in the configuration.

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_TO_CREATE_DATASTORE_CWSJA0020=CWSJA0020E: Unable to create data store.
Message.Explanation: An exception occurred creating a data store with the configuration data provided.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the configuration data provided to create a data store is valid.

Message.MsgText: ENDPOINT_PORT_NOT_SUPPLIED_CWSJA1617=CWSJA1617E: A port has not been supplied for the WebSphere MQ server endpoint
Message.Explanation: A WebSphere MQ server endpoint must have a port.
Message.UserResponse: Set the WebSphere MQ server endpoint port using the "port" parameter.

Message.MsgText: ME_RECOVERY_START_CWSJA0166=CWSJA0166E: The Messaging Engine configuration recovery has started for {0}
Message.Explanation: The Messaging Engine configuration recovery has started.
Message.UserResponse: The Messaging Engine configuration recovery has started.

Message.MsgText: ENGINE_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA0012=CWSJA0012E: The messaging engine "{0}" does not exist at scope "{1}" for bus "{2}".
Message.Explanation: The operation could not be invoked because the given messaging engine does not exist for the given bus at the specified scope.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that a correct messaging engine name and scope are specified.

Message.MsgText: NO_DMGR_CELLS_FOUND_CWSJA1000=CWSJA1000E: Deployment manager configuration contains no cells.
Message.Explanation: No cells were found in the deployment manager configuration.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the deployment manager configuration contains a cell definition.

Message.MsgText: SIB_LINK_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA2403=CWSJA2403E: The SIBLink "{0}" could not be found on the messaging engine "{1}"
Message.Explanation: A SIBLink name was supplied to the command that could not be resolved on the messaging engine name supplied.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that both the messaging engine and SIBLink names supplied to the command exist in the configuration.

Message.MsgText: UNEXPECTED_ERROR_CWSJA0062=CWSJA0062E: An unexpected error has occurred.
Message.Explanation: There is an unexpected problem with the system.
Message.UserResponse: Check the log files for information about the problem.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_SERVER_CHARS_CWSJA0086=CWSJA0086E: The value {0} for the WebSphere MQ queue manager or queue sharing group contains invalid characters.
Message.Explanation: The WebSphere MQ queue manager or queue sharing group allowable characters range a-z, A-Z, 0-9, ., /, % and _.
Message.UserResponse: Run the command again specifying a valid WebSphere MQ queue manager or queue sharing group value.

Message.MsgText: CLUSTER_NOT_COMPATIBLE_WITH_BUS_SECURITY_CWSJA0107=CWSJA0107E: Security settings for bus "{0}" are not compatible with cluster "{1}" because one or more of its member servers reside on a pre-6.1 node.
Message.Explanation: The cluster could not be added to the bus because at least one of its member servers resides on a WebSphere Application Server Version 6.0 node, and bus security settings are not compatible with pre-Version 6.1 nodes. The permitted transport chains setting must not be LISTED or SSL_ENABLED. The group Server must not be in the bus connector role.
Message.UserResponse: Disable security on the named bus, or modify the bus security settings so that bus security is compatible with pre-Version 6.1 nodes, or upgrade the pre-Version 6.1 servers on the named cluster so that they reside on Version 6.1 nodes.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_PARAM_BOOTSTRAP_POLICY_CWSJA0136=CWSJA0136E: bootstrapPolicy setting {0} is not valid. Allowable values MEMBERS_ONLY, SIBSERVICE_ENABLED, MEMBERS_AND_NOMINATED.
Message.Explanation: The supplied parameter bootstrapPolicy has a value that is not valid, so the command was rejected.
Message.UserResponse: Set the bootstrapPolicy to an allowable value of MEMBERS_ONLY, SIBSERVICE_ENABLED, MEMBERS_AND_NOMINATED.

Message.MsgText: BAD_INITIAL_JVM_HEAP_SIZE_CWSJA0143=CWSJA0143E: The new initial JVM heap size value of {0} MB is not in the acceptible range of {1} MB to {2} MB.
Message.Explanation: The supplied initial JVM heap size value is not in the acceptable range.
Message.UserResponse: Change the supplied initial JVM heap size value to one that is in the acceptable range.

Message.MsgText: FILESTORE_NOT_VALID_FOR_VERSION_CWSJA0076=CWSJA0076E: filestore parameter is specified for a messaging engine on a pre version 6.1 node
Message.Explanation: You can only use a file store with a messaging engine on a WebSphere Application Server Version 6.1 or later node.
Message.UserResponse: Select a data store, or choose a node that is of Version 6.1 or later.

Message.MsgText: NEXT_HOP_BUS_REQUIRED_CWSJA2001=CWSJA2001E: The parameter nextHopBus must be specified when routingType = Indirect
Message.Explanation: When the routingType parameter is set to Indirect, a valid nextHopBus parameter must be supplied.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the nextHopBus parameter and value is supplied to the command.

Message.MsgText: SERVER_IS_BUS_MEMBER_CWSJA2610=CWSJA2610E: The server {0} on the node {1} is a bus member.
Message.Explanation: A server cannot be both a bus member and a bootstrap member.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: MQLINK_EXCEPTION_CWSJA2203=CWSJA2203E: An internal error occured getting the "name" attribute of MQLink "{0}" : "{1}"
Message.Explanation: An internal error has occurred. See linked exception for details.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that a valid MQLink name was specified to the command.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_MQLINK_TARGET_OBJECT_CWSJA2208=CWSJA2208E: The target object is not a valid SIB MQLink object.
Message.Explanation: This command requires a valid SIB MQLink object to be passed in as the target object.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the target object of the command is a SIB MQLink object.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_ACT_SPEC_FORWARDER_DOES_NOT_MODIFY_PAYLOAD_VALUE_CWSJA0414=CWSJA0414E: {0} is not a valid value for the parameter: Forwarder does not modify payload after set.
Message.Explanation: A value that is not valid has been entered for this property. Valid values are true and false.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that a valid value is entered for the property.

Message.MsgText: ME_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA0127=CWSJA0127E: A messaging engine for bus "{0}" could not be found on server "{1}".
Message.Explanation: The old bus and server names that were supplied to the command could not be used to resolve a messaging engine object.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that you used the correct spelling for the old bus and server names, and that the server is a member of the old bus.

Message.MsgText: MISSING_FOREIGN_PARAMETER_CWSJA0011=CWSJA0011E: "{0}" must be set to create a foreign destination.
Message.Explanation: An attempt has been made to create an foreign destination without sufficient configuration detail.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that a foreign parameter is specified when creating the foreign destination.

Message.MsgText: BUS_MEMBER_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA0606=CWSJA0606E: Bus member "{0}" cannot be found.
Message.Explanation: The bus member specified could not be located in the administrative domain.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the bus member specified exists before trying to use it.

Message.MsgText: FILESTORE_NOT_VALID_PRE61_CWSJA0101=CWSJA0101E: A file store cannot be specified for a server which is not at version 6.1 or later.
Message.Explanation: The support for a file store is only available on WebSphere Application Server Version 6.1 or later. Either the -fileStore option was specified or another option was set that implied that a file store is to be used.
Message.UserResponse: Run the command again, this time specifying a data store.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_SCOPE_SPECIFICATION_CWSJA0135=CWSJA0135E: Scope specification is not valid.
Message.Explanation: The details specified do not represent a valid scope specification.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that valid node name, server name and cluster name details are used to represent the scope.

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_TO_CREATE_ENGINE_CWSJA0019=CWSJA0019E: Unable to create messaging engine.
Message.Explanation: An exception occurred creating a messaging engine with the configuration data provided.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the configuration data provided to create a messaging engine is valid.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_SSLTYPE_NONE_PARAMETERS_CWSJA1608=CWSJA1608E: The parameters "sslEndpoint", "sslChain", "sslCRL", "sslReset" and "sslPeer" are not valid when the "sslType" parameter is set to "NONE".
Message.Explanation: The parameters "sslEndpoint", "sslChain", "sslCRL", "sslReset" and "sslPeer" are not valid when the "sslType" parameter is set to "NONE".
Message.UserResponse: Specify a different sslType or do not use the illegal parameters.

Message.MsgText: REMOVING_REPLY_DESTINATION_CWSJA0047=CWSJA0047E: Can not have a reply destination bus with out a reply destination name.
Message.Explanation: A reply destination cannot be specified without a reply destination name. The reply destination object will be removed.
Message.UserResponse: If a reply destination is required specify at least the reply destination name.

Message.MsgText: ONLY_ONE_SERVER_BUS_MEMBER_ALLOWED_CWSJA0160=CWSJA0160E: Only one server bus member for each service integration bus can be added as part of the current profile.
Message.Explanation: Multiple server bus members for each service integration bus are not allowed for base profiles.
Message.UserResponse: Review the proposed service integration bus configuration requirements and either adopt a single server bus member for each service integration bus deployment or use multiple server bus members for each service integration bus in a non-base profile.

Message.MsgText: ENDPOINT_HOST_NOR_PORT_NOT_SUPPLIED_CWSJA1620=CWSJA1620E: Neither a host or port has not been supplied for the WebSphere MQ server endpoint
Message.Explanation: At least one of the endpoint attributes must be modified
Message.UserResponse: Supply either a host, port or both parameters.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_ME_ASSISTANCE_PARM_COMBINATION_CWSJA0112=CWSJA0112E: The assistanceEnabled or policyName parameter is missing, when both are required.
Message.Explanation: To use messagine engine policy assistance, set the assistanceEnabled parameter to true and specify a policyName parameter.
Message.UserResponse: Either set the assistanceEnabled parameter to true and specify a valid policyName parameter, or do not use messaging engine policy assistance (set the assistanceEnabled parameter to false).

Message.MsgText: BAD_PARAM_VALUE_CWSJA0159=CWSJA0159E: The useAllMediationPoints parameter can only be set false where mediationPoints contains some values
Message.Explanation: It is not valid to clear this option (setting it false) unless mediationPoints contains at least one mediation point
Message.UserResponse: Either set useAllQueuePoints true, or set mediationPoints to contain at least one mediation point

Message.MsgText: BAD_PARAM_VALUE_CWSJA0158=CWSJA0158E: The useAllQueuePoints parameter can only be set false where queuePoints contains some values
Message.Explanation: It is not valid to clear this option (setting it false) unless queuePoints contains at least one queue point
Message.UserResponse: Either set useAllQueuePoints true, or set queuePoints to contain at least one queue point

Message.MsgText: MQLINK_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA2207=CWSJA2207E: The MQLink "{0}" could not be found on the messaging engine "{1}"
Message.Explanation: An MQLink with the name supplied could not be found on the messaging engine supplied.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that both the messaging engine and MQLink named on the command exist in the configuration.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_PARAM_COMB_CWSJA0082=CWSJA0082E: busSecurity parameter specified with the secure parameter for the modifySIBus command.
Message.Explanation: You cannot specify the busSecurity parameter with the secure parameter.
Message.UserResponse: Remove either the busSecurity or the secure parameter from the modifySIBus command.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_DELETE_JMSQ_NAME_CWSJA0209=CWSJA0209E: Not allowed to delete a SIB JMS queue called "{0}".
Message.Explanation: The name provided for the SIB JMS queue does not adhere to naming restrictions.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the name does not begin with an underscore, and is not empty or null.

Message.MsgText: ENGINE_ALREADY_DEFINED_CWSJA0025=CWSJA0025E: Messaging engine already defined for this bus member.
Message.Explanation: A messaging engine already exists with the configuration data supplied.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that unique configuration data is specified for the messaging engine that is to be created.

Message.MsgText: MISSING_ALIAS_PARAMETER_CWSJA0010=CWSJA0010E: "{0}" must be set to create an alias destination.
Message.Explanation: An attempt has been made to create an alias destination without sufficient configuration detail.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that an alias parameter is specified when creating the alias destination.

Message.MsgText: BAD_PARAM_VALUE_CWSJA0147=CWSJA0147E: The parameter "auditAllowed" is only valid for a destination type which is TopicSpace.
Message.Explanation: The auditAllowed parameter can only be used when the destination type is TopicSpace.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the parameter specified, then reissue the command.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_PORT_VALUE_CWSJA0084=CWSJA0084E: The value {0} for parameter port is not a valid value.
Message.Explanation: Allowable values for the port parameter range between 0 and 65535.
Message.UserResponse: Run the command again specifying a valid port value.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_PARAM_COMB_CWSJA0075=CWSJA0075E: permittedChains parameter specified with the secure parameter for the modifySIBus command
Message.Explanation: You cannot specify the permittedChains parameter with the secure parameter.
Message.UserResponse: Use the busSecurity parameter instead of the secure parameter.

Message.MsgText: MODIFY_FAILED_CWSJA0402=CWSJA0402E: Unable to modify attributes of ActivationSpec {0}.
Message.Explanation: It is likely that incorrect or null parameters were passed to the modify command.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that all parameters passed to the modify command are valid.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_SERVER_LENGTH_CWSJA0085=CWSJA0085E: The value {0} for the WebSphere MQ queue manager or queue sharing group is too long.
Message.Explanation: The maximum length for a WebSphere MQ queue manager or queue sharing group is 48 characters.
Message.UserResponse: Run the command again specifying a valid WebSphere MQ queue manager or queue sharing group value.

Message.MsgText: NO_PARAM_VALUE_CWSJA0036=CWSJA0036E: Required value not supplied for parameter "{1}" of command "{0}".
Message.Explanation: Either the specified parameter was not supplied, or no value was supplied for it.
Message.UserResponse: Run the command again, supplying the missing parameter value.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_CREATE_JMSCF_NAME_CWSJA0206=CWSJA0206E: Not allowed to create a SIB JMS connection factory called "{0}".
Message.Explanation: The name provided for the SIB JMS connection factory does not adhere to naming restrictions.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the name does not begin with an underscore, and is not empty or null.

Message.MsgText: SERVER_DOES_NOT_EXIST_CWSJA2603=CWSJA2603E: The server {0} on node {1} does not exist.
Message.Explanation: The specified server does not exist.
Message.UserResponse: Rerun the command specifying the name of a server and node that exists.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_PARAM_COMB_CWSJA0071=CWSJA0071E: secure parameter specified with scriptCompatibility set to 6.1. Set the scriptCompatibility to 6 when using the secure parameter
Message.Explanation: The secure parameter is not compatible with WebSphere Application Server Version 6.1. The secure parameter is only valid for Version 6.0.
Message.UserResponse: Either set the scriptCompatibility to 6, or use the busSecurity parameter with scriptCompatibility set to 6.1.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_PARAM_COMB_CWSJA0070=CWSJA0070E: busSecurity parameter specified with scriptCompatibility set to 6. Set the scriptCompatibility to 6.1 when using the busSecurity parameter
Message.Explanation: The busSecurity parameter is not compatible with WebSphere Application Server Version 6.0. The busSecurity parameter is only valid for Version 6.1 and later.
Message.UserResponse: Either set the scriptCompatibility to 6.1, or use the secure parameter with scriptCompatibility set to 6.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_CREATE_BUS_NAME_CWSJA0021=CWSJA0021E: The bus with name "{0}" contains invalid characters
Message.Explanation: Bus names cannot contain any of the following characters \/,#$@:;"*?<>|=+&%' or start with _ or . or contain ]]> .
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that a valid bus name is specified for the bus that is to be created.

Message.MsgText: MEDIATION_ALREADY_EXISTS_CWSJA0600=CWSJA0600E: Mediation "{0}" already exists.
Message.Explanation: The mediation specified already exists within the administrative domain.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that all mediations are uniquely identified within an administrative domain.

Message.MsgText: DESTINATION_NOT_MEDIATED_CWSJA0608=CWSJA0608E: Destination "{0}" is not mediated.
Message.Explanation: You cannot un-mediate a destination which is not already mediated.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the destination is mediated before attempting to un-mediate it.

Message.MsgText: CANNOT_CORRECT_POLICY_CWSJA0124=CWSJA0124E: The messaging engine is associated with a server cluster that does not have messaging engine policy assistance enabled, or that has messaging engine policy assistance enabled and the CUSTOM policy specified.
Message.Explanation: To correct a core group policy for a messaging engine, the server cluster that the messaging engine is associated with must have messaging engine policy assistance enabled and the HA, SCALABILITY, or SCALABILITY_HA policy specified.
Message.UserResponse: Either specify a messaging engine that is associated with a server cluster that has messaging engine policy assistance enabled and a valid policy type specified, or use modifySIBusMemberPolicy to modify the server cluster so that assistanceEnabled is true and policyName is set to a valid policy type.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_VIRTUAL_LINK_TYPE_CWSJA2005=CWSJA2005E: The foreign bus "{0}" does not contain a SIBVirtualMQLink child object.
Message.Explanation: The foreign bus specified contains a SIBVirtualGatewayLink, not the required SIBVirtualMQLink.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the foreign bus specified has a SIBVirtualMQLink child object.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_ME_NAME_CWSJA0122=CWSJA0122E: The messaging engine {0} is not valid.
Message.Explanation: You attempted to create a core group policy for a messaging engine when the messaging engine is not associated with a server cluster that is a member of a bus.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the name parameter is the name of a messaging engine that is associated with a server cluster that is a member of a bus.

Message.MsgText: MULTIPLE_BUSES_FOUND_CWSJA0002=CWSJA0002E: Multiple instances of bus "{0}" found.
Message.Explanation: Only one instance of a bus should exist with the name specified, yet more than one instance has been located.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that bus names are unique within the administrative domain.

Message.MsgText: SERVER_NOT_COMPATIBLE_WITH_BOOTSTRAP_POLICY_CWSJA0138=CWSJA0138E: The bootstrap policy for bus "{0}" is not compatible with server "{1}" because it resides on pre-7.0 node "{2}".
Message.Explanation: The server could not be added to the bus because the server resides on a pre-7.0 WebSphere Application Server Version node, and the bootstrap policy setting is not compatible with pre-Version 7.0 nodes. The bootstrap policy setting must not be MEMBERS_ONLY, or MEMBERS_AND_NOMINATED.
Message.UserResponse: Change the bootstrap policy to be SIBSERVICE_ENABLED, or upgrade the named server so that it resides on a Version 7.0 node.

Message.MsgText: DUPLICATE_BUS_UUIDS_CWSJA0029=CWSJA0029E: Failed to find bus. More than one bus found with duplicate UUID.
Message.Explanation: An exception occurred due to multiple buses having identical UUIDs.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that each bus in an administrative domain has a unique UUID.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_DELETE_DEST_NAME_CWSJA0026=CWSJA0026E: Not allowed to delete "{0}" because it is a system destination.
Message.Explanation: The destination with the name specified cannot be deleted.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that a valid destination name is specified for the destination that is to be deleted.

Message.MsgText: ENGINE_NOT_FOUND_WITH_UUID_CWSJA0105=CWSJA0105E: The messaging engine with UUID "{0}" does not exist at scope "{1}".
Message.Explanation: The operation could not be invoked because the messaging engine with the given UUID does not exist at the specified scope.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that there is a messaging engine at the specified scope.

Message.MsgText: MEDIATION_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA0601=CWSJA0601E: Mediation "{0}" cannot be found.
Message.Explanation: The mediation specified could not be found within the administrative domain.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the mediation specified to the command exists.

Message.MsgText: BAD_BUS_BOOTSTRAP_POLICY_VALUE_CWSJA0137=CWSJA0137E: The value "{1}" for the bootstrap member policy bus attribute is not valid for bus "{0}" because the bus contains at least one pre-7.0 bus member.
Message.Explanation: The bootstrap member policies of MEMBERS_ONLY and MEMBERS_AND_NOMINATED are not supported by pre-7.0 nodes, as a result they cannot be specified for a bus that contains pre-7.0 bus members.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a setting that is supported by a bus with pre-7.0 members, or remove all pre7.0 bus members from the bus.

Message.MsgText: NO_ENGINE_NAMES_AVAILABLE_CWSJA0031=CWSJA0031E: No messaging engine names available for cluster.
Message.Explanation: A suitable messaging engine name could not be created.
Message.UserResponse: Try specifying different configuration data when creating the messaging engine.

Message.MsgText: TARGET_OBJECT_OR_TARGET_PARMS_MISSING_CWSJA2502=CWSJA2502E: A target object or target parameters "{0}" must be specified.
Message.Explanation: An AdminTask command is invoked without specifying either a target object or the parameters that are used to specify the target.
Message.UserResponse: Reissue the command either specifying the target object directly, or specifying the target object using the target parameters.

Message.MsgText: MISSING_PARAM_FOR_CLUSTER_CWSJA0064=CWSJA0064E: When creating a {0} on a cluster unable to use default values. The parameter {1} is required
Message.Explanation: Certain default parameters do not apply with clusters, therefore valid values must be specified.
Message.UserResponse: Check that parameters are correct for this message store type on a cluster.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_TYPE_PARAMETER_CWSJA2002=CWSJA2002E: The type parameter must be specified when routingType parameter = Direct
Message.Explanation: When the routingType parameter = Direct, a valid type parameter must be specified.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the type parameter for the command is either SIBus or MQ.

Message.MsgText: GET_RA_FAILED_CWSJA0403=CWSJA0403E: Unable to find SIB JMS resource adapter in scope {0}.
Message.Explanation: It is likely that incorrect or null parameters were passed to the command.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that all parameters are valid, and that a JMS JCA resource adapter is installed at the specified scope.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_PARAM_COMBINATION_CWSJA0098=CWSJA0098E: The parameters "aliasBus" and "foreignBus" were supplied to the deleteSIBDestination command.
Message.Explanation: The deleteSIBDestination command takes either the aliasBus or the foreignBus parameter. The command had both parameters supplied.
Message.UserResponse: If there are multiple destinations with the same name, then the aliasBus or foreignBus parameter can be used to identify either an Alias or a Foreign destination to delete. Only one of the aliasBus or foreignBus parameters can be supplied.

Message.MsgText: BAD_DESTINATION_NAME_CWSJA0042=CWSJA0042E: Not allowed to create a SIBDestination called "{0}"
Message.Explanation: The destination name supplied to the createSIBDestination command is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Run the command again, supplying a valid destination name.

Message.MsgText: CANNOT_ENABLE_WITHOUT_POLICY_CWSJA0116=CWSJA0116E: The assistanceEnabled parameter is set to true but the policyName parameter is missing.
Message.Explanation: To use messagine engine policy assistance, set the assistanceEnabled parameter to true and specify a valid policyName parameter. Valid policy names are HA, SCALABILITY, SCALABILITY_HA, or CUSTOM.
Message.UserResponse: Either specify a valid policy name, or do not use messaging engine policy assistance (set the assistanceEnabled parameter to false).

Message.MsgText: CLUSTER_ALREADY_BUS_MEMBER_CWSJA0130=CWSJA0130E: The cluster "{0}" is already a member of bus "{1}". Messaging engine migration is not supported in this scenario.
Message.Explanation: To migrate a server messaging engine to a cluster, the cluster cannot be a member of the same bus already.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the cluster is not a member of the same bus to which the server belongs.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_ACT_SPEC_TARGET_TYPE_VALUE_CWSJA0411=CWSJA0411E: {0} is not a valid value for target type.
Message.Explanation: A value that is not valid has been entered for the target type property.
Message.UserResponse: Check the documentation for a valid value for this property.

Message.MsgText: ENDPOINT_NOT_SUPPLIED_CWSJA1619=CWSJA1619E: A WebSphere MQ server endpoint has not been supplied as the target object
Message.Explanation: A WebSphere MQ server endpoint must be supplied as the target object
Message.UserResponse: Set a WebSphere MQ server endpoint as the target object.

Message.MsgText: ALREADY_EXISTS_CWSJA0400=CWSJA0400E: ActivationSpec with given name({0}) or jndiName({1}) already exists in given scope.
Message.Explanation: The named ActivationSpec already exists on the specified resource adapter.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that ActivationSpec objects are unique within a given scope.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_ME_POLICY_PARM_COMBINATION_CWSJA0113=CWSJA0113E: The failover, failback, preferredServersOnly, or preferredServerList parameters are not valid.
Message.Explanation: The failover, failback, preferredServersOnly, and preferredServerList parameters are valid only when assistanceEnabled is true and policyName is CUSTOM.
Message.UserResponse: Either set the assistanceEnabled parameter to true and the policyName parameter to CUSTOM, or or do not use these parameters.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_ME_ASSISTANCE_PARM_USE_CWSJA0110=CWSJA0110E: The assistanceEnabled and policyName parameters are not valid when you add a server or WebSphere MQ Server as a bus member.
Message.Explanation: The assistanceEnabled and policyName parameters are valid only when you add a server cluster as a bus member.
Message.UserResponse: Either do not use the assistanceEnabled and policyName parameters, or add a server cluster as a bus member.

Message.MsgText: DUPLICATE_DEST_UUID_CWSJA0032=CWSJA0032E: Failed to find destination. More than one destination with duplicate UUID.
Message.Explanation: More than one destination within the administrative domain has the same UUID.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that each destination within the administrative domain has a unique UUID.

Message.MsgText: VIRTUAL_LINK_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA2401=CWSJA2401E: A virtual link could not be found on foreign bus "{0}"
Message.Explanation: The foreign bus specified to the command does not have a SIBVirtualGatewayLink child object.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the foreign bus specified has a SIBVirtualGatewayLink child object.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_ME_ASSISTANCE_POLICY_NAME_CWSJA0111=CWSJA0111E: The value of policyName {0} is not valid.
Message.Explanation: Valid policy names are HA, SCALABILITY, SCALABILITY_HA, or CUSTOM.
Message.UserResponse: Either specify a valid policy name, or do not use messaging engine policy assistance (set the assistanceEnabled parameter to false).

Message.MsgText: INVALID_PARAM_COMBINATION_CWSJA0063=CWSJA0063E: Can not specify parameter {0} for message store type {1}
Message.Explanation: A file store parameter has been specified for a data store, or a data store parameter has been specified for a file store.
Message.UserResponse: Check that the parameters are correct for this message store type.

Message.MsgText: FAILED_TO_CREATE_JMSQUEUE_CWSJA0215=CWSJA0215E: Failed to create a SIB JMS queue with queue name : "{0}".
Message.Explanation: An instance of a JMS Queue with the specified queue name could not be created.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that a valid queue name has been specified upon creation of the Queue object.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_ACT_SPEC_RETRYINTERVAL_VALUE_CWSJA0415=CWSJA0415E: {0} is not a valid value for retry interval.
Message.Explanation: A value that is not valid has been entered for the retry interval property.
Message.UserResponse: Check the documentation for a valid value for this property.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_MODIFY_POLICY_PARMS_CWSJA0115=CWSJA0115E: The enableAssistance or policyName parameter is missing.
Message.Explanation: To modify messagine engine policy assistance for a cluster, specify either the assistanceEnabled or the policyName parameter.
Message.UserResponse: Specify the assistanceEnabled parameter, the policyName parameter, or both.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_DELETE_ACT_SPEC_NAME_CWSJA0407=CWSJA0407E: Not allowed to delete a SIB JMS ActivationSpec called "{0}".
Message.Explanation: The name provided for the SIB JMS ActivationSpec does not adhere to naming restrictions.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the name does not begin with an underscore, and is not empty or null.

Message.MsgText: DEST_NOT_FOUND_ON_BUS_CWSJA0100=CWSJA0100E: Failed to find destination "{1}" on bus "{0}" with a foreign bus "{2}".
Message.Explanation: The named foreign destination could not be located on the named bus within the administrative domain.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the named foreign destination exists on the named bus with the named foreign bus.

Message.MsgText: SERVER_IS_BOOTSTRAP_MEMBER_CWSJA2611=CWSJA2611E: The server {0} on the node {1} is already a bootstrap member.
Message.Explanation: This message is for informational purposes only.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: CANNOTSTART_MESSAGESTORE_DB_CWSJA0162=CWSJA0162E: The message store for datasource {0} cannot be started.
Message.Explanation: The message store cannot start due to some startup exception.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the datasource value and scope is correct and valid to obtain connection.

Message.MsgText: DMGR_DESTINATION_NOT_SPECIFIED_CWSJA1004=CWSJA1004E: No destination specified.
Message.Explanation: Internal error. Method invoked requires destination object.
Message.UserResponse: Please contact your system administrator to resolve this problem.

Message.MsgText: BAD_RELIABILITY_VALUE_CWSJA0040=CWSJA0040E: The value supplied for "reliability" is greater than the value supplied for "maxReliability".
Message.Explanation: The value supplied for the reliability parameter should be less than or equal to the value supplied for the maxReliability parameter.
Message.UserResponse: Run the command again, supplying a value for the reliability parameter that is less than or equal to the value supplied for the maxReliability parameter.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_PARAMETER_CWSJA2202=CWSJA2202E: The value "{0}" is not valid for the parameter "{1}"
Message.Explanation: A value that is not valid was supplied for the parameter specified above.
Message.UserResponse: See the command help for a list of valid parameter values.

Message.MsgText: DEST_ALREADY_EXISTS_CWSJA0009=CWSJA0009E: Destination "{0}" already exists.
Message.Explanation: The destination specified already exists on the bus.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that destinations on the bus have unique names.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_JMSTOPIC_PROPERTY_VALUE_CWSJA0213=CWSJA0213E: Not allowed to configure a SIB JMS topic with "{0}" = "{1}".
Message.Explanation: The value provided for the specified JMS Topic property is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the value specified is allowed for the given property.

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_TO_MEDIATE_DEST_CWSJA0081=CWSJA0081E: Unable to mediate destination {0} as the WebSphere MQ queue name {1} cannot be used as both the mediation and queue points.
Message.Explanation: When mediating a destination that has a message point on WebSphere MQ, the pre-mediation point MQ queue name must not be the same as the message point MQ queue name.
Message.UserResponse: Choose a different WebSphere MQ destination from which the mediation is to get messages.

Message.MsgText: CLUSTER_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA0128=CWSJA0128E: The cluster "{0}" could not be found.
Message.Explanation: The cluster name that were supplied to the command could not be used to resolve a Cluster object.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that you used the correct spelling for the cluster name, and that the Cluster exists in the configuration.

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_TO_CREATE_DATASOURCE_CWSJA0016=CWSJA0016E: Unable to create data source.
Message.Explanation: An exception occurred creating a data source with the configuration data provided.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the configuration data provided to create a data source is valid.

Message.MsgText: ENDPOINT_HOST_NOT_SUPPLIED_CWSJA1616=CWSJA1616E: A host has not been supplied for the WebSphere MQ server endpoint
Message.Explanation: A WebSphere MQ server endpoint must have a host.
Message.UserResponse: Set the WebSphere MQ server endpoint host using the "host" parameter.

Message.MsgText: FAILED_TO_CREATE_JMSCF_CWSJA0217=CWSJA0217E: An internal error has occurred. Failed to create a SIB JMS connection factory.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: CLUSTER_NOT_SUPPORTING_BOOTSTRAP_MEMBERS_CWSJA2606=CWSJA2606E: The cluster {0} contains servers that do not support bootstrap members. The servers are on the nodes: {1}.
Message.Explanation: In order for clusters to be bootstrap members all the servers in the cluster must be on a node whose version is at least 7.0.0.0.
Message.UserResponse: This can be resolved either by upgrading all the nodes, or by choosing a different cluster.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_CREATE_JMST_NAME_CWSJA0210=CWSJA0210E: Not allowed to create a SIB JMS topic called "{0}".
Message.Explanation: The name provided for the SIB JMS Topic does not adhere to naming restrictions.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the name does not begin with an underscore, and is not empty or null.

Message.MsgText: DUPLICATE_NAMESPACE_ENTRY_CWSJA2404=CWSJA2404E: There is already a SIBLink or MQLink with the name "{0}"
Message.Explanation: SIBLink and MQLink objects share a namespace within a messaging engine, and require unique names.
Message.UserResponse: If you want to use the supplied name, ensure that neither an MQLink nor SIBLink already exists with that name. Otherwise, specify a different name.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_DELETE_JMSCF_NAME_CWSJA0207=CWSJA0207E: Not allowed to delete a SIB JMS connection factory called "{0}".
Message.Explanation: The name provided for the SIB JMS connection factory does not adhere to naming restrictions.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the name does not begin with an underscore, and is not empty or null.

Message.MsgText: BUILT_IN_PROVIDER_CWSJA1605=CWSJA1605E: The selected JMS provider is built-in and cannot be deleted.
Message.Explanation: Only custom JMS providers can be deleted.
Message.UserResponse: Select a different JMS provider to delete.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_NODE_ME_VERSION_FOR_PREFER_LOCAL_CWSJA2407=CWSJA2407E: The messaging engine "{0}" is running in a v6.1 or earlier server. The preferLocal attribute can only be set to true when the server running the messaging engine is v7.0.
Message.Explanation: The preferLocal attribute can only be set to true when the server running the messaging engine is v7.0.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the messaging engine hosting the link is running on a v7.0 server before setting the preferLocal attribute to true.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_ACT_SPEC_PARAM_VALUE_COMBINATION_CWSJA0418=CWSJA0418E: The failingMessageDelay value can only be greater than zero if autoStopSequentialMessageFailure is greater than zero.
Message.Explanation: The message delay is only used when sequential message failures are being monitored and the MDB endpoint can be automatically stopped.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a value of zero for the failingMessageDelay or a positive value for autoStopSequentialMessageFailure.

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_TO_CREATE_RESOURCE_PROPERTYSET_CWSJA0017=CWSJA0017E: Unable to create resource property set.
Message.Explanation: An exception occurred creating a resource property set with the configuration data provided.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the configuration data provided to create a resource property set is valid.

Message.MsgText: BUS_ALREADY_EXISTS_CWSJA0000=CWSJA0000E: Bus "{0}" already exists.
Message.Explanation: Bus names must be unique within the administrative domain.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a name for this bus that is not already in use within the administrative domain.

Message.MsgText: FOREIGNBUS_NAME_SAME_AS_LOCAL_BUS_CWSJA2010=CWSJA2010E: The name of the foreign bus cannot be the same as the local bus name "{0}" on which it is to be created.
Message.Explanation: When creating a foreign bus, its name cannot be the same as the local bus on which it is being created. The name should be the unique name of the foreign bus to which you are connecting.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the name parameter supplied is different to the bus parameter.

Message.MsgText: NODE_NOT_SUPPORTING_BOOTSTRAP_MEMBERS_CWSJA2609=CWSJA2609E: The node {0} does not support bootstrap members.
Message.Explanation: In order for a server to be a bootstrap member the node it is defined to needs to have a version that is at least 7.0.0.0.
Message.UserResponse: This can be resolved either by upgrading the nodes, or by choosing a server on a different node.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_SCOPE_SPECIFICATION_CWSJA2405=CWSJA2405E: Scope specification is not valid.
Message.Explanation: The details specified do not represent a valid scope specification.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that valid node name, server name and cluster name details are used to represent the scope.

Message.MsgText: CREATE_FAILED_CWSJA0401=CWSJA0401E: Unable to create SIB JMS ActivationSpec at scope {0}.
Message.Explanation: The create command ran but no result object was returned.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the correct configuration information has been passed to the create command being run.

Message.MsgText: NO_FAILOVER_MEANS_PINNED_SERVER_CWSJA0118=CWSJA0118E: If a messaging engine cannot fail over, it must run on one preferred server.
Message.Explanation: The failover parameter is set to false but either the preferredServersOnly parameter is set to false or the preferredServerList parameter does not specify one server.
Message.UserResponse: Either ensure that the preferredServersOnly parameter is set to true and the preferredServerList parameter specifies one server, or set the failover parameter to true.

Message.MsgText: SUBSCRIPTIONID_MANDATORY_PARAMETER_CWSJA0170=CWSJA0170E: The subscriptionId parameter is mandatory for republishing messages to a destination of type TopicSpace.
Message.Explanation: The subscriptionId parameter is mandatory for republishing messages to a destination of type TopicSpace.
Message.UserResponse: Add the subscriptionId parameter to the command and rerun the command.

Message.MsgText: SCOPE_NOT_A_BUSMEMBER_CWSJA0103=CWSJA0103E: The specified scope "{0}" is not a member of bus "{1}".
Message.Explanation: The operation could not be invoked because the specified server or cluster is not a member of the given bus.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that a server or cluster is specified that is a member of the given bus.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_PARAM_COMBINATION_CWSJA0007=CWSJA0007E: Incorrect parameter combination supplied : node name = "{0}", server name = "{1}", cluster name = "{2}", WebSphere MQ server name = "{3}".
Message.Explanation: The parameters supplied do not provide a valid bus member configuration.
Message.UserResponse: To correctly identify a bus member, specify node name and server name, or cluster name, or WebSphere MQ server name.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_SSLTYPE_TYPE_SUPPLIED_CWSJA1612=CWSJA1612E: The sslType {0} is not valid (valid values are "NONE", "CENTRAL", "SPECIFIC" and "CHAIN").
Message.Explanation: Valid values for the sslType parameter are "NONE", "CENTRAL", "SPECIFIC" and "CHAIN".
Message.UserResponse: Set the sslType parameter to be either "NONE", "CENTRAL", "SPECIFIC" or "CHAIN"

Message.MsgText: WMQ_SERVER_NOT_SUPPLIED_CWSJA1606=CWSJA1606E: A WebSphere MQ server has not been supplied as the target object
Message.Explanation: A WebSphere MQ server must be supplied as the target object
Message.UserResponse: Set a WebSphere MQ server as the target object.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_PARAM_TRANSPORT_CWSJA0074=CWSJA0074E: Invalid permittedChains setting {0}. Allowable values ALL|SSL_ENABLED|LISTED
Message.Explanation: The supplied parameter permittedChains has a value that is not valid, so the command was rejected.
Message.UserResponse: Set the permittedChains to an allowable value of ALL, SSL_ENABLED or LISTED.

Message.MsgText: NO_BUS_MEMBER_CWSJA0614=CWSJA0614E: No bus member found for WebSphere MQ server {0} on bus {1}.
Message.Explanation: When mediating a destination using a WebSphere MQ server it must have been added to the bus, but no bus member was found.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the WebSphere MQ server has been added to the bus specified then retry the command.

Message.MsgText: INCONSISTENT_CONFIG_DETECTED_CWSJA0607=CWSJA0607E: Destination "{0}" cannot be mediated.
Message.Explanation: An inconsistent configuration has been detected.
Message.UserResponse: Run cross document validation to check the destination configuration.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_JMSQUEUE_PROPERTY_VALUE_CWSJA0212=CWSJA0212E: Not allowed to configure a SIB JMS queue with "{0}" = "{1}".
Message.Explanation: The value provided for the specified JMS Queue property is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the value specified is allowed for the given property.

Message.MsgText: BUS_ALREADY_EXISTS_ON_DMGR_CWSJA0802=CWSJA0802W: WARNING: Bus "{0}" already exists in the deployment manager configuration. Bus "{0}" will NOT be replaced in the deployment manager configuration.
Message.Explanation: A bus of the same name already exists in the deployment manager configuration. As a result the bus on this node will not be added to the deployment manager configuration. However the node will still be federated.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the named bus does not exist in the deployment manager configuration before running the addNode command. If there is a conflict in the names, the bus on the node being federated is not included. As a result the bus on the deployment manager must be configured to have the required resources needed. Either that, or the bus should be renamed or deleted.

Message.MsgText: ME_RECOVERY_COMPLETE_CWSJA0167=CWSJA0167E: The Messaging Engine configuration recovery for {0} is complete.
Message.Explanation: The Messaging Engine configuration recovery is complete.
Message.UserResponse: The Messaging Engine configuration recovery is complete.

Message.MsgText: CONFIG_SERVICE_NOT_AVAILABLE_CWSJA2500=CWSJA2500E: The configuration service is not available.
Message.Explanation: An AdminTask command is trying to work with a process that is not connected to a server that has a running configuration service.
Message.UserResponse: Reissue the command on a process that is connected to a server that has a running configuration service. For example a deployment manager, managed server or unmanaged server.

Message.MsgText: BAD_PARAM_COMBINATION_CWSJA0057=CWSJA0057E: The WebSphere MQ queue name parameter must be specified for a destination on a WebSphere MQ Server
Message.Explanation: When creating a destination on a WebSphere MQ server the wmqQueueName parameter must be specified.
Message.UserResponse: Change the destination type to be QUEUE then retry the command.

Message.MsgText: BAD_PARAM_COMBINATION_CWSJA0056=CWSJA0056E: The WebSphere MQ Server name parameter can only be specified with a destination type of QUEUE, the type specified was "{0}"
Message.Explanation: When creating a destination the WebSphere MQ server name was specified with a destination type other than QUEUE.
Message.UserResponse: Change the destination type to be QUEUE then retry the command.

Message.MsgText: BAD_PARAM_COMBINATION_CWSJA0055=CWSJA0055E: The parameter {0} with value {1} is not valid when specifying a WebSphere MQ Server name.
Message.Explanation: The supplied parameter is not valid when creating a destination. The parameter supplied is only valid when not specifying a WebSphere MQ server name.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the parameter from the createSIBDestination command then retry the command.

Message.MsgText: BAD_PARAM_COMBINATION_CWSJA0054=CWSJA0054E: The parameter {0} with value {1} is only valid when specifying a WebSphere MQ Server name.
Message.Explanation: The supplied parameter is not valid when creating a destination. The parameter supplied is only valid when specifying a WebSphere MQ server name.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the parameter from the createSIBDestination command then retry the command.

Message.MsgText: NO_DMGR_SESSION_SUPPLIED_CWSJA1001=CWSJA1001E: No deployment manager configuration session supplied.
Message.Explanation: Internal error. Method invoked requires a deployment manager configuration session parameter.
Message.UserResponse: Please contact your system administrator to resolve this problem.

Message.MsgText: BAD_PARAM_COMBINATION_CWSJA0053=CWSJA0053E: The parameter {0} is only valid when specifying a WebSphere MQ Server name.
Message.Explanation: The supplied parameter is not valid when adding a server or a cluster to a bus.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the parameter from the addSIBusMember command then retry the command.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_REPLYTOQUEUE_LENGTH_CWSJA0096=CWSJA0096E: The value {0} for the WebSphere MQ reply to queue is too long.
Message.Explanation: The maximum length for a WebSphere MQ reply to queue is 48 characters.
Message.UserResponse: Run the command again specifying an allowable WebSphere MQ reply to queue value.

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_TO_CREATE_MQ_SERVER_PROXY_CWSJA0050=CWSJA0050E: Unable to create WebSphere MQ Server Bus Member.
Message.Explanation: An exception occurred creating a WebSphere MQ server bus member with the configuration data provided.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the configuration data provided to create a WebSphere MQ server bus member is valid.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_SSLTYPE_CENTRAL_PARAMETERS_CWSJA1609=CWSJA1609E: The parameters "sslEndpoint" and "sslChain" are not valid when the "sslType" parameter is set to "CENTRAL".
Message.Explanation: The parameters "sslEndpoint" and "sslChain" are not valid when the "sslType" parameter is set to "CENTRAL".
Message.UserResponse: Specify a different sslType or do not use the illegal parameters.

Message.MsgText: BAD_TYPE_CWSJA0201=CWSJA0201E: Incorrect value for type parameter: {0}.
Message.Explanation: An incorrect type has been found for the connection factory.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the connection factory type is either Queue, Topic or All.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_BUS_MEMBER_CWSJA0018=CWSJA0018E: Bus member supplied is not a member of the specified bus.
Message.Explanation: The specified bus member is not a member of this bus.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the specified bus member is a member of this bus.

Message.MsgText: BAD_PARAM_COMBINATION_CWSJA0044=CWSJA0044E: Node, server, WebSphere MQ Server and/or cluster supplied when type is "WebServices".
Message.Explanation: The node, server and cluster parameters should not be specified when the type is WebServices.
Message.UserResponse: Run the command again, supplying a valid combination of parameters.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_CLUSTER_MEMBER_CWSJA0114=CWSJA0114E: Server {1} on node {0} is not a member of cluster {2}.
Message.Explanation: You specified a server in the preferred servers list when that server is not a member of the current cluster.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the servers specified for the preferredServerList parameter are members of the current cluster.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_CHANNEL_CHARS_CWSJA0088=CWSJA0088E: The value {0} for the WebSphere MQ channel contains invalid characters.
Message.Explanation: The WebSphere MQ queue channel allowable characters range a-z, A-Z, 0-9, ., /, % and _.
Message.UserResponse: Run the command again specifying a valid WebSphere MQ channel value.

Message.MsgText: BUS_MEMBER_ALREADY_EXISTS_CWSJA0003=CWSJA0003E: Bus member "{0}" already exists.
Message.Explanation: An attempt has been made to add a server to a bus of which it is already a member.
Message.UserResponse: Do not attempt to add a bus member if the server in question is already a member.

Message.MsgText: DESTINATION_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA0603=CWSJA0603E: Destination "{0}" cannot be found.
Message.Explanation: The destination specified could not be found within the administrative domain.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the specified destination exists.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_SEND_EXIT_PARAMETERS_SUPPLIED_CWSJA1613=CWSJA1613E: The "sendExitInit" parameter can only be supplied if the "sendExit" parameter is supplied.
Message.Explanation: The "sendExitInit" parameter can only be supplied if the "sendExit" parameter is supplied.
Message.UserResponse: Supply the "sendExit" parameter or do not suplly the "sendExitInit" parameter.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_TARGET_DEST_LP_CWSJA0157=CWSJA0157E: The target destination for an Alias destination must not be localized on an MQ Server.
Message.Explanation: It is not valid to supply a target destination for an Alias destination that is localized on an MQ Server.
Message.UserResponse: Supply a target destination that is not localized on an MQ Server.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_DEFAULT_PRIORITY_CWSJA2006=CWSJA2006E: The default priority specified "{0}" is not a valid value for this attribute.
Message.Explanation: The value of the default priority attribute must be between 0 and 9 inclusive.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that a valid value is specified for the default priority attribute.

Message.MsgText: MSG_ORDER_NOT_VALID_PRE61_CWSJA0102=CWSJA0102E: The maintainStrictMessageOrder option cannot be used for a destination that has all its message points on servers of a version less than 6.1.
Message.Explanation: The option to maintain strict message order is only available on WebSphere Application Server Version 6.1 or later.
Message.UserResponse: Run the command again. Only specify strict message ordering if you also specify a server of Version 6.1 or later.

Message.MsgText: CANNOT_DISABLE_WITH_POLICY_CWSJA0117=CWSJA0117E: A policyName parameter is specified when the assistanceEnabled parameter is set to false.
Message.Explanation: To disable messaging engine policy assistance, set the assistanceEnabled parameter to false and do not specify a policyName parameter.
Message.UserResponse: Either set the assistanceEnabled parameter to false and do not specify a policyName parameter, or set the assistanceEnabled parameter to true and specify a valid policyName parameter.

Message.MsgText: BAD_TARGET_CWSJA0205=CWSJA0205E: Target object is not a SIB JMS topic.
Message.Explanation: The interface of the target object is not of type Topic.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the target object is of type Topic.

Message.MsgText: BAD_TARGET_CWSJA0204=CWSJA0204E: Target object is not a SIB JMS queue.
Message.Explanation: The interface of the target object is not of type Queue.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the target object is of type Queue.

Message.MsgText: BAD_TARGET_CWSJA0203=CWSJA0203E: Target object is not a SIB JMS connection factory.
Message.Explanation: The target object specified is not of type QueueConnectionFactory, TopicConnectionFactory or ConnectionFactory.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that a valid connection factory interface is specified to the target object.

Message.MsgText: USE_SERVER_IDENTITY_FOR_MEDIATIONS_NOT_SUPPORTED_CWSJA0142=CWSJA0142E: The bus {0} could not be modified to use the server identity for mediations as it contains members that reside on pre-Version 7.0 nodes.
Message.Explanation: The bus contains servers or clusters that run on pre-Version 7.0 nodes. The userServerIdForMediations option does not support pre-Version 7.0 nodes so the command could not complete.
Message.UserResponse: Upgrade the pre-Version 7.0 nodes.

Message.MsgText: MQ_SERVER_NAME_NOT_UNIQUE_CWSJA1602=CWSJA1602E: A WebSphere MQ Server named "{0}" already exists.
Message.Explanation: A WebSphere MQ server name must be unique. A WebSphere MQ server with the supplied name already exists.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that WebSphere MQ server names are unique within the administrative domain.

Message.MsgText: BUSMEMBER_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA0023=CWSJA0023E: Bus member not found.
Message.Explanation: The bus member specified could not be located within the administrative domain.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that a valid bus member is being located.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_MESSAGING_SERVER_CWSJA0033=CWSJA0033E: Server supplied does not have a SIB service.
Message.Explanation: No SIB services were found for this messaging server.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that a SIB service exists for this messaging server.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_CHANNEL_LENGTH_CWSJA0087=CWSJA0087E: The value {0} for the WebSphere MQ channel is too long.
Message.Explanation: The maximum length for a WebSphere MQ channel is 20 characters.
Message.UserResponse: Run the command again specifying a valid WebSphere MQ channel value.

Message.MsgText: NOT_SIB_JMS_ACT_SPEC_CWSJA0405=CWSJA0405E: {0} is not a valid SIB JMS ActivationSpec.
Message.Explanation: The target object specified is not of the correct type.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the target object is of type JMS ActivationSpec.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_SCOPE_SPECIFICATION_CWSJA0090=CWSJA0090E: Scope specification is not valid, unable to locate cluster {0}.
Message.Explanation: The details specified do not represent a valid scope specification.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that valid cluster name details are used to represent the scope.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_DELETE_BUS_NAME_CWSJA0022=CWSJA0022E: Not allowed to delete a bus called "{0}".
Message.Explanation: An exception has occurred attempting to delete a bus with the name specified.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that a valid bus name is specified for the bus that is to be deleted.

Message.MsgText: CHAIN_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA0078=CWSJA0078E: The transport chain name {0} was not found as a permitted transport for the bus {1}.
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to remove a permitted transport from a bus. However the specified permitted transport chain is not a permitted transport for the specified bus.
Message.UserResponse: If the permitted transport exists on the bus, check and correct the name then reissue the command.

Message.MsgText: CHAIN_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA0073=CWSJA0073E: The permitted transport chain name {0} was not found
Message.Explanation: The permitted transport chain with the specified name was not found on the bus.
Message.UserResponse: Use the administrative console to check that the transport chain name exists and that the case of the name is correct, then reissue the command.

Message.MsgText: BUS_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA2200=CWSJA2200E: The bus name "{0}" could not be found.
Message.Explanation: The bus name that was supplied to the command could not be resolved to a Bus object.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that you used the correct spelling for the name, and that a Bus with that name exists in the configuration.

Message.MsgText: UNSUPPORTED_TYPE_CWSJA0006=CWSJA0006E: Destination type "{0}" is not supported by this command.
Message.Explanation: An incorrect destination type has been specified.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the destination type specified is valid.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_CREATE_MEDIATION_NAME_CWSJA0609=CWSJA0609E: Not allowed to create a mediation called "{0}".
Message.Explanation: The name provided for the mediation does not adhere to naming restrictions.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the name does not begin with an underscore, and is not empty or null.

Message.MsgText: SVRCONN_CHANNEL_NAME_NOT_SUPPLIED_CWSJA1607=CWSJA1607E: A name has not been supplied for the WebSphere MQ server SVRCONN channel
Message.Explanation: A WebSphere MQ server SVRCONN channel must have a name.
Message.UserResponse: Set the WebSphere MQ server SVRCONN channel name using the "name" parameter.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_SCOPE_SPECIFICATION_CWSJA0089=CWSJA0089E: Scope specification is not valid, unable to locate node {0} and or server {1}.
Message.Explanation: The details specified do not represent a valid scope specification.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that valid node and server name details are used to represent the scope.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_ACT_SPEC_CONSUMER_DOES_NOT_MODIFY_PAYLOAD_VALUE_CWSJA0413=CWSJA0413E: {0} is not a valid value for the parameter: Consumer does not modify payload after get.
Message.Explanation: A value that is not valid has been entered for this property. Valid values are GuaranteedByUser and NotGuaranteedByUser.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that a valid value is entered for the property.

Message.MsgText: INITIAL_JVM_HEAP_SIZE_BIGGER_THAN_MAX_JVM_HEAP_SIZE_CWSJA0146=CWSJA0146E: The new initial JVM heap size value of {0} is bigger than the new maximum JVM heap size value of {1}.
Message.Explanation: The supplied initial JVM heap size value is bigger than the supplied maximum JVM heap size value.
Message.UserResponse: Change the supplied initial and maximum JVM heap size values so that the initial JVM heap size value is not be bigger than the maximum JVM heap size value.

Message.MsgText: SIB_JDBCPROVIDER_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA0015=CWSJA0015E: SIB JDBC provider not found.
Message.Explanation: An attempt has been made to locate a SIB JDBC provider within the scope provider, but none was found.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that there is a SIB JDBC provider available within the administrative domain.

Message.MsgText: SIBLINK_FOREIGN_BUS_ALREADY_USED_CWSJA2408=CWSJA2408E: The foreign bus "{0}" is already in use by another SIBLink.
Message.Explanation: The foreign bus specified already contains a reference to a SIBLink.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that a foreign bus is specified that doesn't reference a pre-existing SIBLink.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_SSLTYPE_CHAIN_PARAMETERS_CWSJA1611=CWSJA1611E: The "sslChain" parameter is not valid when the "sslType" parameter is set to "CHAIN".
Message.Explanation: The "sslChain" parameter is not valid when the "sslType" parameter is set to "CHAIN".
Message.UserResponse: Specify a different sslType or do not use the illegal parameters.
