Message.MsgText: INVALID_ACT_SPEC_READAHEAD_VALUE_CWSJA0409=CWSJA0409E: {0} is not a valid value for read ahead.
Message.Explanation: A value that is not valid has been entered for the read ahead property.
Message.UserResponse: Check the documentation for a valid value for this property.

Message.MsgText: BAD_RELIABILITY_VALUE_CWSJA2007=CWSJA2007E: The value supplied for "reliability" is greater than the value supplied for "maxReliability".
Message.Explanation: The value supplied for the reliability parameter should be less than or equal to the value supplied for the maxReliability parameter.
Message.UserResponse: Report this problem to your system administrator.

Message.MsgText: ENGINE_EXISTS_CWSJA0004=CWSJA0004E: Messaging engine "{0}" already exists.
Message.Explanation: The messaging engine specified already exists on the server.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the messaging engine details are not identical to that of another messaging engine on the server.

Message.MsgText: NO_ENGINE_NAMES_AVAILABLE_CWSJA0132=CWSJA0132E: No messaging engine names available for cluster.
Message.Explanation: A suitable messaging engine name could not be created.
Message.UserResponse: Try specifying different configuration data when creating the messaging engine.

Message.MsgText: GENERIC_EXCEPTION_OCCURED_CWSJA0169=CWSJA0169E: The JMS_IBM_ExceptionProblemDestination or JMS_IBM_ExceptionTimestamp parameters are not allowed in the selection criteria.
Message.Explanation: The JMS_IBM_ExceptionProblemDestination or JMS_IBM_ExceptionTimestamp parameters are reserved for internal use when running the command.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that you are not using the JMS_IBM_ExceptionProblemDestination or JMS_IBM_ExceptionTimestamp parameters in the selection criteria. Modify the selection criteria and rerun the command.

Message.MsgText: GENERIC_EXCEPTION_OCCURED_CWSJA0168=CWSJA0168E: A generic exception occurred while processing the command parameters.
Message.Explanation: Unable to query the MBeans objects.
Message.UserResponse: Check if the session is connected successfully using the specified connection parameters.

Message.MsgText: CLUSTER_IS_BUS_MEMBER_CWSJA2607=CWSJA2607E: The cluster {0} is a bus member.
Message.Explanation: A cluster cannot be both a bus member and a bootstrap member.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_PARAM_COMBINATION_CWSJA2009=CWSJA2009E: The routingType parameter is required if the type parameter is supplied.
Message.Explanation: The type parameter is only permitted if the routingType parameter is also supplied.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the routingType parameter is supplied if the type parameter is supplied.

Message.MsgText: MULTIPLE_ENGINES_FOUND_CWSJA0013=CWSJA0013E: Multiple messaging engines were found.
Message.Explanation: Multiple messaging engines have been found matching the configuration data provided.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that messaging engines are unique within the administrative domain.

Message.MsgText: TARGET_OBJECT_AND_TARGET_PARMS_SPECIFIED_CWSJA2501=CWSJA2501E: Target object and target parameters "{0}" can not be both specified.
Message.Explanation: An AdminTask command is specifying both a target object and one of the parameters that is used to specify the target.
Message.UserResponse: Reissue the command either specifying the target object directly, or specifying the target object using the target parameters.

Message.MsgText: SVRCONN_CHANNEL_NOT_SUPPLIED_CWSJA1621=CWSJA1621E: A WebSphere MQ server server connection channel has not been supplied as the target object
Message.Explanation: A WebSphere MQ server server connection channel must be supplied as the target object
Message.UserResponse: Set a WebSphere MQ server server connection channel as the target object.

Message.MsgText: FAILOVER_ON_PREF_SERVER_ONLY_ERROR_CWSJA0120=CWSJA0120E: If a messaging engine can fail over to preferred servers only, there must be at least two servers in the preferred servers list.
Message.Explanation: The failover parameter is set to true and the preferredServersOnly parameter is set to true, but the the preferredServerList parameter does not specify at least two servers (one to run on, and one to fail over to).
Message.UserResponse: Either ensure that the preferredServerList parameter specifies at least two servers, or set the preferredServersOnly parameter to false.

Message.MsgText: CLUSTER_IS_BOOTSTRAP_MEMBER_CWSJA2608=CWSJA2608E: The cluster {0} is already a bootstrap member.
Message.Explanation: This message is for informational purposes only.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_ACT_SPEC_AUTO_STOP_SEQ_MSG_FAILURE_VALUE_CWSJA0416=CWSJA0416E: The autoStopSequentialMessageFailure value, {0}, is not an valid integer value greater than or equal to zero.
Message.Explanation: Valid values are zero which indicates that MDB endpoints will not be automatically stopped. Or one or more, which indicates the number of failing sequential messages that will cause the MDB endpoint to be stopped.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a value of zero or more.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_TYPE_VALUE_CWSJA2008=CWSJA2008E: An invalid type parameter was supplied to this command, allowable values are "MQ" or "SIBus".
Message.Explanation: The type of either MQ or SIBus is required for this command.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the type parameter for the command is either MQ or SIBus.

Message.MsgText: SERVER_NOT_A_BOOTSTRAP_MEMBER_CWSJA2605=CWSJA2605E: The server {0} on node {1} is not a bootstrap member.
Message.Explanation: The specified server is not a bootstrap member, so cannot be removed from the list of bootstrap members.
Message.UserResponse: Rerun the command specifying the name of a server and node that is a bootstrap member.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_DELETE_JMST_NAME_CWSJA0211=CWSJA0211E: Not allowed to delete a SIB JMS topic called "{0}".
Message.Explanation: The name provided for the SIB JMS topic does not adhere to naming restrictions.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the name does not begin with an underscore, and is not empty or null.

Message.MsgText: MEDIATION_IN_USE_CWSJA0602=CWSJA0602E: Mediation "{0}" cannot be deleted. It is being used to mediate destination "{1}".
Message.Explanation: A mediation cannot be deleted whilst it is being used to mediate a destination.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that a mediation is not being used before trying to delete it.

Message.MsgText: ME_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA2201=CWSJA2201E: The messaging engine "{0}" could not be found on the bus supplied.
Message.Explanation: A messaging engine name was supplied to the command that could not be resolved on the bus name supplied.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that both the messaging engine and bus name supplied to the command exist in the configuration.

Message.MsgText: BUS_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA0001=CWSJA0001E: Bus "{0}" not found.
Message.Explanation: The specified bus name could not be located within the administrative domain.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the bus name specified is a valid bus name for an existing bus.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_FILESTORE_SIZE_CWSJA0092=CWSJA0092E: Can not specify maximum temporary file store size if unlimited temporary store size is set to true.
Message.Explanation: When the size of the temporary file store has been set to unlimited, a maximum temporary size cannot be set.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the maximum temporary file store size parameter or change the unlimited temporary file store size to false then retry.

Message.MsgText: ENDPOINT_PORT_NOT_VALID_CWSJA1618=CWSJA1618E: A valid value must be supplied for the endpoint port.
Message.Explanation: A valid value must be supplied for the endpoint port.
Message.UserResponse: Set the WebSphere MQ server endpoint with a valid port number.

Message.MsgText: DEST_ALREADY_SPECIFIED_CWSJA0145=CWSJA0145E: Duplicate destination "{0}" in nameList.
Message.Explanation: The given destination is specified more than once in the nameList.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the destinations specified in the nameList are unique.

Message.MsgText: CLUSTER_NOT_A_BOOTSTRAP_MEMBER_CWSJA2604=CWSJA2604E: The cluster {0} is not a bootstrap member.
Message.Explanation: The specified cluster is not a bootstrap member, so cannot be removed from the list of bootstrap members.
Message.UserResponse: Rerun the command specifying the name of a cluster that is a bootstrap member.

Message.MsgText: BAD_PARAM_VALUE_CWSJA0091=CWSJA0091E: The parameter "topicAccessCheckRequired" is only valid for a destination type which is TopicSpace.
Message.Explanation: The topicAccessCheckRequired parameter can only be used when the destination type is TopicSpace.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the parameter specified, then reissue the command.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_VIRTUAL_LINK_TYPE_CWSJA2402=CWSJA2402E: The foreign bus "{0}" does not contain a SIBVirtualGatewayLink child object.
Message.Explanation: The foreign bus specified contains a SIBVirtualMQLink, not the required SIBVirtualGatewayLink.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the foreign bus specified has a SIBVirtualGatewayLink child object.

Message.MsgText: SUBSCRIPTIONID_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA0171=CWSJA0171E: The subscriptionId {0} provided in the command is currently not active on any of the publication points of the topic space {1}.
Message.Explanation: SubscriptionId is a mandatory parameter for republishing messages to a destination of type TopicSpace. The subscriptionId provided in the command is not found to be active on any of the publication points of the topic space.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that a valid subscription Id that is active is provided as an input to the command and rerun the command.

Message.MsgText: DEST_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA0080=CWSJA0080E: Destination {0} not found on bus {1}.
Message.Explanation: The specified destination could not be found on the specified bus.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the destination being located exists within the administrative domain.

Message.MsgText: MISSING_PARAM_CWSJA0065=CWSJA0065E: Can not create a {0} without a value for {1}
Message.Explanation: A value for the specified parameter is required to create a message store of this type.
Message.UserResponse: Check that the parameters are correct for this message store type.

Message.MsgText: BAD_PARAM_VALUE_CWSJA0083=CWSJA0083E: The parameter {0} is only valid for a destination type which is either a Queue, Port or WebService
Message.Explanation: The parameter supplied can only be used when the destination type is Queue, Port or WebService.
Message.UserResponse: Run the command again without using the previously stated parameter.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_DELETE_MEDIATION_NAME_CWSJA0610=CWSJA0610E: Not allowed to delete a mediation called "{0}".
Message.Explanation: The name provided for the mediation does not adhere to naming restrictions.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the name does not begin with an underscore, and is not empty or null.

Message.MsgText: SIBMQLINK_FOREIGN_BUS_ALREADY_USED_CWSJA2409=CWSJA2409E: The foreign bus "{0}" is already in use by another MQLink.
Message.Explanation: The foreign bus specified already contains a reference to a MQLink.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that a foreign bus is specified that doesn't reference a pre-existing MQLink.

Message.MsgText: DMGR_BUS_NOT_SPECIFIED_CWSJA1003=CWSJA1003E: No bus specified.
Message.Explanation: Internal error. Method invoked requires a bus object.
Message.UserResponse: Please contact your system administrator to resolve this problem.

Message.MsgText: MISMATCH_DATASOURCE_SCOPE_CWSJA0165=CWSJA0165E: The scope of the data source {0} does not match the scope of ME recovery.
Message.Explanation: The recovery of ME config cannot be done because scope of datasource does not match scope of given nodename or clustername
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that scope of given datasource matches scope of clustername or nodename

Message.MsgText: INVALID_PARAM_COMBINATION_CWSJA0156=CWSJA0156E: The "queuePoints" and "mediationPoints" parameters can only be specified when the type of the destination is ALIAS.
Message.Explanation: It is not valid to supply either queuePoints or mediationPoints when the destination type is not set to ALIAS.
Message.UserResponse: Only supply "queuePoints" or "mediationPoints" when the destination type is set to ALIAS.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_PARAM_COMBINATION_CWSJA0154=CWSJA0154E: The "mediationPoints" parameter can only be used when the target destination is a queue destination with one or more mediation points.
Message.Explanation: Specifying mediation points is only permitted when the alias directly targets a Queue destination localized to a bus member with multiple messaging engines.
Message.UserResponse: Do not supply the "mediationPoints" parameter, or supply it and target a Queue destination localized to a bus member with multiple messaging engines.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_PARAM_COMBINATION_CWSJA0153=CWSJA0153E: The "mediationPoints" parameter can only be used when the target destination is in the same bus as the alias destination definition.
Message.Explanation: Specifying mediation points is only permitted when the alias directly targets a Queue destination in the same bus as the alias definition (the 'bus' parameter).
Message.UserResponse: Do not supply the "mediationPoints" parameter, or supplpy it and target a Queue destination in the same bus as the alias definition.

Message.MsgText: BAD_PARAM_VALUE_CWSJA0079=CWSJA0079E: Incorrect value "{0}" for parameter "scriptCompatibility".
Message.Explanation: The value supplied for the parameter scriptCompatibility is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Run the command again, supplying a value that is either 6 (for compatability with WebSphere Application Server Version 6.0) or 6.1 (for compatability with Version 6.1).

Message.MsgText: FOREIGN_BUS_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA2204=CWSJA2204E: The foreign bus "{0}" could not be found on the bus "{1}"
Message.Explanation: The foreign bus name supplied to the command is not the name of a foreign bus configured on the bus.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that both the foreign bus and bus name supplied to the command exist in the configuration.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_PARAM_COMBINATION_CWSJA0152=CWSJA0152E: The "mediationPoints" parameter can only be used when the target destination is an existing queue destination.
Message.Explanation: Specifying mediation points is only permitted when the alias directly targets a Queue destination.
Message.UserResponse: Do not supply the "mediationPoints" parameter, or supply it and target a Queue destination.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_PARAM_COMBINATION_CWSJA0150=CWSJA0150E: The "queuePoints" parameter can only be used when the target destination is a queue destination with one or more queue points.
Message.Explanation: Specifying queue points is only permitted when the alias directly targets a Queue destination localized to a bus member with multiple messaging engines.
Message.UserResponse: Do not supply the "queuePoints" parameter, or supply it and target a Queue destination localized to a bus member with multiple messaging engines.

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_TO_CREATE_FILESTORE_CWSJA0060=CWSJA0060E: Unable to create file store.
Message.Explanation: A file store could not be created with the configuration data provided.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the configuration data provided to create a file store is valid.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_ROUTING_TYPE_PARAMETER_CWSJA2003=CWSJA2003E: An invalid routingType parameter was supplied to this command, allowable values are "Direct" or "Indirect".
Message.Explanation: The routingType of either Direct or Indirect is required for this command.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the routingType parameter for the command is either Direct or Indirect.

Message.MsgText: INCORRECT_RELIABILITY_VALUE_CWSJA2011=CWSJA2011E: The value "{0}" is not a valid value for the attribute "{1}". Valid values for "{1}" are BEST_EFFORT_NONPERSISTENT, EXPRESS_NONPERSISTENT, RELIABLE_NONPERSISTENT, RELIABLE_PERSISTENT or ASSURED_PERSISTENT.
Message.Explanation: An incorrect value has been supplied. Valid values are BEST_EFFORT_NONPERSISTENT, EXPRESS_NONPERSISTENT, RELIABLE_NONPERSISTENT, RELIABLE_PERSISTENT or ASSURED_PERSISTENT. These values are case sensitive.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure the a valid value is supplied to the command.

Message.MsgText: CLUSTER_NOT_COMPATIBLE_WITH_BOOTSTRAP_POLICY_CWSJA0139=CWSJA0139E: The bootstrap policy for bus "{0}" is not compatible with cluster "{1}" because it has members that reside on pre-7.0 nodes.
Message.Explanation: The cluster could not be added to the bus because the cluster has members that reside on a pre-7.0 WebSphere Application Server Version node, and the bootstrap policy setting is not compatible with pre-Version 7.0 nodes. The bootstrap policy setting must not be MEMBERS_ONLY, or MEMBERS_AND_NOMINATED.
Message.UserResponse: Change the bootstrap policy to be SIBSERVICE_ENABLED, or upgrade the named cluster so that all servers in the cluster reside on a Version 7.0 node.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_ACT_SPEC_TARGET_SIGNIFICANCE_VALUE_CWSJA0412=CWSJA0412E: {0} is not a valid value for target significance.
Message.Explanation: A value that is not valid has been entered for the target significance property.
Message.UserResponse: Check the documentation for a valid value for this property.

Message.MsgText: ME_POLICY_ASSISTANCE_DISABLED_CWSJA0123=CWSJA0123E: The messaging engine is associated with a server cluster that does not have messaging engine policy assistance enabled and the CUSTOM policy specified.
Message.Explanation: To create a core group policy for a messaging engine, the server cluster that the messaging engine is associated with must have messaging engine policy assistance enabled and the CUSTOM policy specified.
Message.UserResponse: Either specify a messaging engine that is associated with a server cluster that has messaging engine policy assistance enabled and the CUSTOM policy specified, or use modifySIBusMemberPolicy to modify the server cluster so that messaging engine policy assistance is enabled and the CUSTOM policy is specified.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_PARAM_COMBINATION_CWSJA0149=CWSJA0149E: The "queuePoints" parameter can only be used when the target destination is in the same bus as the alias destination definition.
Message.Explanation: Specifying queue points is only permitted when the alias directly targets a Queue destination in the same bus as the alias definition (the 'bus' parameter).
Message.UserResponse: Do not supply the "queuePoints" parameter, or supply it and target a Queue destination in the same bus as the alias definition.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_PARAM_COMBINATION_CWSJA0148=CWSJA0148E: The "queuePoints" parameter can only be used when the target destination is an existing queue destination.
Message.Explanation: Specifying queue points is only permitted when the alias directly targets a Queue destination.
Message.UserResponse: Do not supply the "queuePoints" parameter, or supply it and target a Queue destination.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_FILESTORE_SIZE_CWSJA0059=CWSJA0059E: Can not specify maximum permanent file store size if unlimited permanent store size is set to true
Message.Explanation: When the size of the permanent file store has been set to unlimited, a maximum permanent size cannot be set.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the maximum permanent file store size parameter or change the unlimited permanent file store size to false then retry.

Message.MsgText: LIST_FAILED_CWSJA0404=CWSJA0404E: Failed to get list of existing SIB JMS ActivationSpecs from resource adapter {0}.
Message.Explanation: The list command was unsuccessful either because null parameters were given, or no result was returned.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that all parameters passed to the command are valid, and not null.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_SSLTYPE_SPECIFIC_PARAMETERS_CWSJA1610=CWSJA1610E: The "sslChain" parameter is not valid when the "sslType" parameter is set to "SPECIFIC".
Message.Explanation: The "sslChain" parameter is not valid when the "sslType" parameter is set to "SPECIFIC".
Message.UserResponse: Specify a different sslType or do not use the illegal parameters.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_REPLYTOQUEUE_CHARS_CWSJA0097=CWSJA0097E: The value {0} for the WebSphere MQ reply to queue contains invalid characters.
Message.Explanation: The WebSphere MQ reply to queue allowable characters range a-z, A-Z, 0-9, ., /, % and _.
Message.UserResponse: Run the command again specifying an allowable WebSphere MQ reply to queue value.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_FILE_SIZE_CWSJA0095=CWSJA0095E: Maximum temporary store size can not be less than minimum temporary store size.
Message.Explanation: An attempt is being made to configure a maximum temporary store size with a value that is less than the minimum temporary store size.
Message.UserResponse: Either lower the minimum temporary store size, increase the maximum temporary store size, or make the maximum temporary store size unlimited.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_FILE_SIZE_CWSJA0094=CWSJA0094E: Maximum temporary store size must be greater than {0} megabytes.
Message.Explanation: The maximum temporary store size specified is lower than the maximum temporary store size minimum value.
Message.UserResponse: Increase the size of the maximum temporary store size, or make it unlimited.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_FILE_SIZE_CWSJA0093=CWSJA0093E: Minimum temporary store size can not be less than log size.
Message.Explanation: The temporary file store size must be greater than the temporary store log size.
Message.UserResponse: Increase the temporary store size or decrease the log size.

Message.MsgText: DMGR_CELL_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA0801=CWSJA0801E: No cells found in the deployment manager configuration.
Message.Explanation: The deployment manager configuration does not contain any cells.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the deployment manager configuration contains a cell.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_SCOPE_SPECIFICATION_CWSJA0008=CWSJA0008E: Scope specification is not valid.
Message.Explanation: The details specified do not represent a valid scope specification.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that valid node name, server name and cluster name details are used to represent the scope.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_PARAM_COMBINATION_CWSJA0133=CWSJA0133E: Incorrect parameter combination supplied : node name = "{0}", server name = "{1}", cluster name = "{2}".
Message.Explanation: The parameters supplied do not provide a valid bus member configuration.
Message.UserResponse: To correctly identify a bus member, specify node name and server name, or cluster name.

Message.MsgText: BAD_MAX_JVM_HEAP_SIZE_CWSJA0144=CWSJA0144E: The new maximum JVM heap size value of {0} MB is not in the acceptible range of {1} MB to {2} MB.
Message.Explanation: The supplied maximum JVM heap size value is not in the acceptable range.
Message.UserResponse: Change the supplied maximum JVM heap size value to one that is in the acceptable range.

Message.MsgText: DMGR_CELL_NOT_SPECIFIED_CWSJA1002=CWSJA1002E: No cell specified.
Message.Explanation: Internal error. Method invoked requires a cell object.
Message.UserResponse: Please contact your system administrator to resolve this problem.

Message.MsgText: COMMAND_FAILED_CWSJA0202=CWSJA0202E: Failed to get J2C command result: {0}.
Message.Explanation: The command was run but no result object was returned.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the correct configuration information has been passed to the command being run.

Message.MsgText: POLICY_CANNOT_CHANGE_WHEN_ASSIST_DISABLED_CWSJA0121=CWSJA0121E: You can not change the messaging engine policy when messaging engine policy assistance is disabled.
Message.Explanation: You specified a new policyName parameter when the assistanceEnabled parameter is set to false.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the assistanceEnabled parameter is set to true, then specify a valid policyName parameter.

Message.MsgText: MQ_SERVER_ALREADY_MEMBER_OF_BUS_CWSJA0049=CWSJA0049E: WebSphere MQ server "{0}" is already a member of bus "{1}".
Message.Explanation: An attempt has been made to add an MQ server to a bus of which it is already a member.
Message.UserResponse: Do not try to add an WebSphere MQ server to a bus of which it is already a member.

Message.MsgText: CANNOTSTART_MESSAGESTORE_FILE_CWSJA0163=CWSJA0163E: The message store for file store {0} cannot be started.
Message.Explanation: The message store cannot start due to some startup exception.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that file store path is correct and reachable.

Message.MsgText: DEST_NOT_FOUND_ON_BUS_CWSJA0099=CWSJA0099E: Failed to find destination "{1}" on bus "{0}" with an alias bus "{2}".
Message.Explanation: The named alias destination could not be located on the named bus within the administrative domain.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the named alias destination exists on the named bus with the named alias bus.

Message.MsgText: BAD_PARAM_VALUE_CWSJA0043=CWSJA0043E: The value of {2} is not valid for parameter {1} when destination type is {0}.
Message.Explanation: The value supplied for the specified parameter is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Run the command again, supplying a valid value.

Message.MsgText: SERVER_NOT_BUS_MEMBER_CWSJA0131=CWSJA0131E: The server "{1}" on node "{0}" is not a member of the bus "{2}".
Message.Explanation: The node and server supplied to the command do not correspond to a member of the bus supplied.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that you used the correct spelling for the node, server and bus name, and that the server is a member of the bus.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_CLUSTER_ME_VERSION_FOR_PREFER_LOCAL_CWSJA2406=CWSJA2406E: The messaging engine "{0}" is running in a cluster that contains one or more v6.1 or earlier servers. The preferLocal attribute can only be set to false when a cluster running the messaging engine contains only v7.0 servers.
Message.Explanation: The preferLocal attribute can only be set to false when a cluster running the messaging engine contains only v7.0 servers.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the messaging engine hosting the link is running in a cluster containing only v7.0 servers before setting the preferLocal attribute to false.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_DATASOURCE_SCOPE_CWSJA0164=CWSJA0164E: The scope of the data source {0} is invalid.
Message.Explanation: The message store cannot start due to some startup exception.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that scope of given datasource is valid

Message.MsgText: BAD_PARAM_VALUE_CWSJA0037=CWSJA0037E: Incorrect value "{2}" for parameter "{1}" of command "{0}".
Message.Explanation: The value supplied for the specified parameter of the specified command is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Run the command again, supplying a valid value.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_FILE_SIZE_CWSJA0069=CWSJA0069E: Maximum permanent store size can not be less than minimum permanent store size
Message.Explanation: Maximum store size cannot be less than minimum store size.
Message.UserResponse: Either lower the minimum store size, or increase the maximum store size, or make the maximum store size unlimited.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_FILE_SIZE_CWSJA0068=CWSJA0068E: Maximum permanent store size must be greater than {0} megabytes
Message.Explanation: The maximum permanent store size specified is lower than the maximum permanent store size minimum value.
Message.UserResponse: Increase the size of the maximum permanent store size, or make it unlimited.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_FILE_SIZE_CWSJA0067=CWSJA0067E: Log size must be greater than {0} megabytes
Message.Explanation: The log size specified is lower than the minimum log size.
Message.UserResponse: Increase the size of the log file.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_FILE_SIZE_CWSJA0066=CWSJA0066E: Minimum permanent store size can not be less than log size
Message.Explanation: The permanent file store size must be greater than the file store log size.
Message.UserResponse: Increase the permanent store size or decrease the log size.

Message.MsgText: DEST_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA0027=CWSJA0027E: Destination {0} not found on bus {1}.
Message.Explanation: An exception occurred attempting to locate the specified destination.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the destination being located exists within the administrative domain.

Message.MsgText: FAILED_TO_CREATE_JMSTOPIC_CWSJA0216=CWSJA0216E: Failed to create a SIB JMS topic with topic name : "{0}".
Message.Explanation: An instance of a JMS topic with the specified topic name could not be created.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that a valid topic name has been specified upon creation of the Topic object.

Message.MsgText: BAD_GROUP_IN_BUS_CONNECTOR_ROLE_CWSJA0109=CWSJA0109E: Found group "Server" in the bus connector role for bus "{0}". This is not allowed because the bus contains at least one pre-6.1 bus member.
Message.Explanation: The named bus contains one or more WebSphere Application Server Version 6.0 bus members. Having the named group in the bus connector role is not compatible with pre-Version 6.1 bus members. The Server group must not be in the bus connector role.
Message.UserResponse: Disable security on the named bus, or remove the named group from the bus connector role, or remove all pre-Version 6.1 bus members from the bus.

Message.MsgText: BUS_MEMBER_TARGET_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA2206=CWSJA2206E: A Bus Member Target with an Engine UUID of "{0}" could not be found
Message.Explanation: The messaging engine UUID specified above could not be found on any of the existing bus member targets.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the correct messaging engine was supplied to the command.

Message.MsgText: BAD_PARAM_COMBINATION_CWSJA0617=CWSJA0617E: When specifying a value of true for parameter "externallyMediated" and a WebSphere MQ server, the "node", "server" or "cluster" parameters should not be specified.
Message.Explanation: Externally mediating destinations are only supported for destinations that are localized in WebSphere MQ.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the node, server or cluster parameter that was specified.

Message.MsgText: BAD_PARAM_COMBINATION_CWSJA0616=CWSJA0616E: When specifying a value of true for parameter "externallyMediated" a "wmqServer" parameter must be supplied.
Message.Explanation: External mediation support is only valid for destinations localized to WebSphere MQ.
Message.UserResponse: Either specify a false value for the externallyMediated parameter or add a wmqServer parameter.

Message.MsgText: VIRTUAL_LINK_NOT_FOUND_CWSJA2004=CWSJA2004E: A virtual link could not be found on foreign bus "{0}"
Message.Explanation: The foreign bus specified to the command does not have a virtual link child object.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the foreign bus specified has a virtual link child object.

Message.MsgText: BAD_PARAM_COMBINATION_CWSJA0613=CWSJA0613E: When specifying a WebSphere MQ Server name using the "wmqServer" parameter the "wmqQueueName" parameter must be supplied.
Message.Explanation: When specifying a WebSphere MQ server name a WebSphere MQ Queue name must be supplied.
Message.UserResponse: Add the wmqQueueName parameter to the mediateSIBDestination command then retry.

Message.MsgText: BAD_PARAM_COMBINATION_CWSJA0612=CWSJA0612E: The parameter {0} is only valid when specifying a WebSphere MQ Server name using the "wmqServer" parameter.
Message.Explanation: The supplied parameter is not valid when mediating a destination and a WebSphere MQ server name was not specified.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the parameter from the mediateSIBDestination command then retry.
